:[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezk:30:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"In the eleventh year, in the first month, on the seventh day of the month, the word of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" came to me: "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezk:30:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Son of man, I have broken the arm "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 10:15","book":"Psa","chapter":10,"verse":15,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 37:17","book":"Psa","chapter":37,"verse":17,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Pharaoh king of Egypt. Look, it has not been bandaged —no medicine has been applied and no splint put on to bandage it so that it can grow strong enough to handle a sword. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 10:15","book":"Psa","chapter":10,"verse":15},{"label":"Ps 37:17","book":"Psa","chapter":37,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezk:30:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Therefore, this is what the Lord "},{"kind":"text","text":"God","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" says: Look! I am against Pharaoh king of Egypt. I will break his arms, both the strong one and the one already broken, and will make the sword fall from his hand. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezk:30:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will disperse the Egyptians among the nations and scatter them among the countries. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 29:12","book":"Ezk","chapter":29,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ezk 29:12","book":"Ezk","chapter":29,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezk:30:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will strengthen the arms of Babylon’s king and place my sword "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Zp 2:12","book":"Zep","chapter":2,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" in his hand. But I will break the arms of Pharaoh, and he will groan before him as a mortally wounded man. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Zp 2:12","book":"Zep","chapter":2,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezk:30:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will strengthen the arms of Babylon’s king, but Pharaoh’s arms will fall. They will know that I am the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" when I place my sword in the hand of Babylon’s king and he wields it against the land of Egypt. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezk:30:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When I disperse the Egyptians among the nations and scatter them among the countries, they will know that I am the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":".”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783279584925}